Your hair like this.

04:47.125 --> 04:50.917
Yeah, you look like a star.

25:01.667 --> 25:02.542
Hello.

25:05.583 --> 25:06.792
What’s your name?

25:12.458 --> 25:13.875
Teddy Bear.

25:23.500 --> 25:25.042
No, not that name.

25:27.208 --> 25:28.958
Your real name.

25:35.208 --> 25:36.167
Miguel.

25:41.458 --> 25:43.667
Miguel Aguilar.

25:45.292 --> 25:47.042
Nice to meet you, Miguel.

25:50.708 --> 25:51.625
Come with me.

26:26.958 --> 26:28.208
That’s a Mustang.

26:28.958 --> 26:31.167
That’s a very fast car.

26:36.125 --> 26:37.333
I’m hungry.

26:39.750 --> 26:41.625
Wanna get a burger?

26:44.250 --> 26:45.208
Let me guess.

26:46.542 --> 26:50.417
You’re seven and a half.

26:53.000 --> 26:54.083
Is it April?

26:54.458 --> 26:57.750
No. It’s July. July 12. Why?

27:00.792 --> 27:02.583
Then I’m eight.

27:12.417 --> 27:14.875
I’ve got a son just your age.

27:16.042 --> 27:17.292
His name’s Kalen.

27:18.750 --> 27:19.917
And I’m Tim.

27:21.000 --> 27:21.958
Tim Ballard.

27:23.083 --> 27:26.750
But you can call me Timoteo.

27:29.167 --> 27:30.375
Timoteo?

27:32.125 --> 27:34.292
That’s my name in Spanish, right?

27:48.458 --> 27:50.083
